  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to define if palliative surgery in patients with cancer improves
      quality of life and prognosis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to find out if palliative surgery in patients with cancer
      improves quality of life and prognosis. There will be a scheduled assessment of quality of
      life and assessment of postoperative complications. prognostic scoring will be performed
      before surgical intervention.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
